      <div class="cbt-editorial-review">
        <p class="cbt-quote-text">“The CBT Flip Chart makes it so easy for therapy clients to learn and apply the big-picture treatment approaches that will help them most. Clients love visual aids, and this engaging tool can be used either to introduce key strategies or to work systematically through a current problem. Clients can use dry-erase markers to interact with the laminated pages, and the more detailed therapist pages offer prompts or examples to help clients internalize the material. This is an outstanding resource that makes the process of therapy straightforward, productive, and rewarding for clients and therapists alike.”</p>
        <span class="cbt-quote-author">—Joel Minden, PhD, psychologist and author of Show Your Anxiety Who's Boss</span>
      </div>

      <div class="cbt-editorial-review">
        <p class="cbt-quote-text">“Dr. Seth Gillihan has created an indispensable tool for therapists. The CBT Flip Chart takes the best lessons from psychological science and makes them accessible through beautifully illustrated pages filled with practical coping tools. Dr. Gillihan’s Think Act Be framework includes essential strategies for challenging unhelpful thoughts, initiating behavioral activation, and practicing mindfulness. The therapist-facing pages include multiple relatable examples to facilitate effective explanations to clients. The client-facing pages provide well-structured frameworks for the practice and personalization of the treatment tools. Dr. Gillihan’s compassionate approach to bolstering mental health shines throughout each page. I’m excited to use this outstanding resource with my clients! ”</p>
        <span class="cbt-quote-author">—Kathryn H. Gordon, PhD, clinical psychologist and author of The Suicidal Thoughts Workbook</span>
      </div>
    </section>

